field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Reshma4, Trimi1, Soff4A, Stoff4B, Stoff4C, Stoff4E, Stoff4F. Stoff are Ru(18)O2 sputtered today at 400 C

notes: 01... Stoff4E way too hairy. Want nicer-looking data for the overnight run. 02... Stoff4F periodic air bubbles instead. I can work with this. Left running overnight. Problems with data transfer prove to be due to U-drive connectivity failure! Perhaps there is no problem with the potentiostat communications after all, and the issue just comes when trying to save directly on the Network drive? Can't really see any exchange... Electrolyte collected. -------- 19J21 -------- 01... Reshma4F looks fine, no exchange. Required Teflon tape around the sides of the electrode to get it to sit in the cell. 02.. through 04... Fuck, tilty Pt CV's! Cleaned out the spilled electrolyte from the clamping ring between 02 and 03. CHanged chip in the process, to B2. Dissassembled and saw it was completely wet inside u-cup behind electrode between 03 and 04. The latter helps, but the CV's are still tiltly! The measured OCV makes sense for Pt but is also close to the intersection of the tilt. If I can't get a decent Pt CV, I can't trust anything. Changing u-cup this time. Again, there was a bit of eectolyte in the u-cup. I think it's been deformed by the Teflon tape used with Reshma4F. 05... Much better! Cathodic region a bit below zero, but improves as air signal falls, indicating it is real ORR... Centered after I get a coffee. Got a few cycles at lower scan rate and a CO strip to check if capacitance is always fucked on this setup or just for Cu or just when the u-cup isn't tight enough or what. mass-transport-limited HOR current is about half of what it should be! I should test this with the spacer at some point to prove the o-ring increases working distance. Not today, though. RE_vs_RHE = 0.656 (This IS significantly different than the old electrolyte, for which I find a calibration of RE_vs_RHE=0.685) 5 minutes at 100 uA. Doesn't stabilize. I think RuOx has higher FE for OER under this experiment than Pt. No sign of Koper's third H desorption peak. 06... Stoff 4A damn, seems there's no exchange on these 400C Ru(18)O2 films. The labeling is only evidenced by the m/z=46 in the advantitious carbon. Otherwise experiment is going good! Bumped alligator clip a bit while collecting the 2 min sample, potential jumped. 10 min extraction goes perfectly, can't even see it in the potential. 07... Stoff4B, 30 uA Waiting a bit longer with Stoff4C, for lower background. 08... Stoff4C, 10 uA Damn, there seems to be almost 10 uA worth of CO2 the whole way through. 09... Easter1C, 100 uA, overnight I'm not really hapy about how much that OCP is moving! But the CV looks okay, with a sharp start. Low apacitance, though! As low as Stoff. Easter should be much higher. Oh, it looks like shit. Yes! Clear lattice O evolution. A good way to end the day :D I am a bit in doubt about whether the whole electrode is wet because of the low cap and noise in the CV. It probably is, since the potential is just below 0.8 V vs RE, whereas it was just above for Stoff at the same current density. In any case, this will have to do. I have a date. 10... Stoff1D. Multipoint goes smooth, don't see any exchange. Can not get clear extraction! CO oxidation activity increases after scanning into H region No exchange in final OER either 11... Easter1B Can't really see any exchange at 30 uA. Lost control, OCP goes crazy after withdrawing electrolyte, big air signals. Starting over. 12... Easter1B Clear exchange at 100 uA! Again no clear exchange at 30 uA. Integrating will tell. 13... Easter1D Wanted an activity and exchange vs potential measurement with the last Easter. Need Teflon tape between u-cup and cell to hold it in place. Fuck, absolutely terrible tilt. Tilt is changinging, too. Whatever, just gonna let it run while I set up the theta probe. ... Stoff4G: rinsed in milliQ like the others.
